============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is capitalism?
A1: Capitalism is an economic system where private
     individuals own the means of production and markets
     determine prices and production through supply and
     demand.

Q2: What is machine learning?
A2: Machine learning enables systems to learn from
     experience without being explicitly programmed, using
     data to improve performance automatically.

Q3: What is entropy?
A3: Entropy measures disorder or randomness in a system.
     The Second Law of Thermodynamics states it always
     increases in isolated systems — the arrow of time.

Q4: What is metabolism?
A4: Metabolism is all chemical reactions in an organism
     that maintain life: catabolism (breaking molecules for
     energy) and anabolism (building complex molecules from
     simple ones).

Q5: What is osmosis?
A5: Osmosis is the movement of water across a semi-
     permeable membrane from high water concentration to low
     water concentration (high solute to low solute) until
     equilibrium.

